main event: Multiple unidentified objects were tracked by military radar in the Michigan-Wisconsin area on 18 September 1951.
interesting points: The observation lasted for approximately 2 hours,The objects were described as flying at high speeds with erratic courses,The objects were believed to possibly be balloons or aircraft due to weather conditions,Several reliable witnesses reported seeing a circular, glowing object around 30 feet in diameter,The radar observations showed objects performing sudden accelerations and sharp turns.
